                        <div class="col-md-12">
                            <p>
                                My research lies at the intersection of <strong>security, privacy, and AI</strong>,
                                with a primary mission to ensure the safety and trustworthiness of emerging AI
                                technologies.
                            </p>

                            <p>
                                My group focuses on three interconnected challenges in the era of Generative AI and
                                Foundation Models:
                            </p>

                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Defending Against AI-Enabled Threats:</strong> Investigating how attackers
                                    leverage recent advances—such as
                                    multimodal LLMs—to generate harmful content or compromise systems.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Securing AI Infrastructure:</strong> Uncovering vulnerabilities in machine
                                    learning supply chains
                                    and model deployment to prevent adversarial attacks and backdoors.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>AI for Defense:</strong> Leveraging the reasoning capabilities of modern AI
                                    to build
                                    more dynamic and resilient security protections.
                                </li>
                            </ul> 
                            
                            <br>
                            
                            <p>
                                <strong> I am a recipient of the Distinguished Paper Award (USENIX Security'25),
                                    Distinguished Paper Award (SOUPS 2014), Best Paper Award (COSN 2015), and the <a
                                        href="https://www.aminer.org/ai2000/cn">AI2000 Most Influential Scholar Award
                                        Honorable Mention</a> for being among the top 100 most cited scholars in
                                    computer networking from 2009-2019.</strong>
                                <br>
                                <br>
                                I completed my Ph.D. in Computer Science at the&nbsp;<a
                                    href="https://www.mpi-sws.org/">Max Planck Institute for Software Systems</a>.
                                Before joining VT, I spent ~2 years as a Postdoc in <a
                                    href="http://sandlab.cs.uchicago.edu/">SAND lab</a> (at <a
                                    href="https://www.cs.ucsb.edu/">UCSB</a>). Prior to that, I spent a year as a
                                Researcher at&nbsp;<a href="https://www.bell-labs.com/">Nokia Bell Labs,
                                    Stuttgart</a>.
                                <br>
                                <br>
                                Our research is supported by CCI, NSF and 4-VA.
                            </p>
                            
